HEADWORD: Dabb
<hw>Dabb</hw> <pr>(d⟦adot⟧b)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large, spine-tailed lizard (<spn>Uromastix spinipes</spn>), found
in Egypt, Arabia, and Palestine; -- called also
<altname>dhobb</altname>, and <altname>dhubb</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dabber</ent>⟦br⟧
